.TH DISCORD_NEXT_EVENT 3 "2026-06-29" "libdiscord 0.1.0" "libdiscord Programmer's Manual"
.SH NAME
discord_next_event \\\\- retrieve next Discord protocol event from the context's queue
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
#include <discord.h>

int discord_next_event(discord_ctx_t *ctx, discord_event_t *event);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Dequeues the next event (if any) into the caller-provided \\\\fBdiscord_event_t\\\\fP structure and returns 1. Returns 0 if the queue is empty or on invalid arguments (NULL ctx or event).

Gateway lifecycle events:
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_READY \\\\(em Gateway READY received (user_id, session_id, gateway_url)
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_CONNECTED \\\\(em Binary channel established (Gateway or API)
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_DISCONNECTED \\\\(em Gateway disconnected (WebSocket close)

Message events:
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_MESSAGE_CREATE \\\\(em New message (id, channel_id, guild_id, author_id, content, timestamp)
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_MESSAGE_UPDATE \\\\(em Message edited
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_MESSAGE_DELETE \\\\(em Message deleted

Other events:
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_GUILD_CREATE \\\\(em Guild info received
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_INTERACTION_CREATE \\\\(em Slash command / component interaction
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_API_RESPONSE \\\\(em REST API response (status_code, json_body, body_len)
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_ERROR \\\\(em Error with detail string
.IP \\(bu 2
DISCORD_EVENT_RAW \\\\(em Raw unparseable WebSocket frame
.SH RETURN VALUES
1 if an event was copied into *event, 0 otherwise.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
discord_event_t ev;
while (discord_next_event(bot, &ev) == 1) {
    switch (ev.type) {
    case DISCORD_EVENT_MESSAGE_CREATE:
        printf("Message: %s\\n", ev.data.message.content);
        break;
    case DISCORD_EVENT_READY:
        printf("Ready! Session: %s\\n", ev.data.ready.session_id);
        break;
    case DISCORD_EVENT_API_RESPONSE:
        printf("API response: %d (%zu bytes)\\n",
               ev.data.api_response.status_code,
               ev.data.api_response.body_len);
        break;
    case DISCORD_EVENT_ERROR:
        fprintf(stderr, "Error: %s\\n", ev.error_msg);
        break;
    default: break;
    }
}
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
discord_create(3), discord_feed_input(3), discord_create_message(3), discord_event_t(3)
.SH NOTES
Data pointers in events are valid only until the next discord_feed_input or discord_destroy call. The library emits raw JSON for API responses; caller owns all parsing and policy (per ADR 006).
